a different type of SQL Server object such as a stored procedure, a view, or even a database. Indeed, it
can even be a server-level object such as a device or login.
// Get a reference to the table. Notice that schema is actually the *2nd*
// parameter
// not the first.
Table Employee = db.Tables["Employee", "HumanResources"];
